Senior Credit Manager
Job Seekers
|
|
what:
where:
Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank Ltd
-
Abu Dhabi
Provide an all in risk assessment in accordance with ADCB (UCC) principles for a designated portfolio. Recommend the approval /rework and or rejection of a credit proposal based on the merits of the case. Provide quality assessments to minimize any intervention by ensuring that the filtering of poor or inadequate applications prior to the submission to the Team Leader; however the rejection of any application after a recommendation requires dual A and B signatories consent. Ensure that all data presented by the Business Unit in terms of the grading of financial and other subjective /objective elements are correct and in keeping with industry standards. Ensure no loan losses on credits approved due to poor credit assessment. Ensure the integrity of Bank’s portfolio in terms of ADCB’s Credit and Risk Appetite Policies. All exceptions to be clearly highlighted and exception sought from the approving authority
In accordance with ADCB’s strategic initiative ensuring that the average rating of the portfolio does not deteriorate, but rather improve with credits approved and that the new assets booked improve the overall portfolio rating and RAROC. Closely monitorallocated portfolio to ensure that portfolio loan loss provisions are minimised, if necessary by the identification /restructuring of loans exhibiting incipient signs of impairment via discussions with the Team Leaders and Business Units. Ensure that each Credit proposal identifies the three to four triggers that shall be monitored periodically to ensure that the quality of the Credit Risk underwritten does not deteriorate. For control purposes to ensure that trigger breach is immediately identified and escalated to ensure a proactive remedial intervention before it spirals out of control. To provide leadership in all aspects of the job to credit officers /credit analysts and /or any other new/junior staff. Assist in the development of systems and other projects as required.
